As of the 2000 [[census]],<ref name="GR2" /> 8 people, 4 households, and 2 families were residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was 1.4 people per square mile (0.5/km{{sup|2}}), with 12 housing units at an average density of 2.0/sq&nbsp;mi (0.8/km{{sup|2}}). The racial makeup of the CDP was 100.00% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], and therefore no individuals were from other races nor any from two or more races, although 75.00% of the population were [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] (included in the white race category).{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}

Out of a total of 4 households, 25.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 50.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, and 50.0% were non-families. 50.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 25.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.00 and the average family size was 3.00.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 12.5% under the age of 18, 12.5% from 18 to 24, 25.0% from 25 to 44, 37.5% from 45 to 64, and 12.5% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 47 years. For every 100 females, there were 33.3 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 40.0 males.{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}

The median income for a household in the CDP was [[USD|US$]]51,250, and the median income for a family was [[USD|US$]]51,250. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was [[USD|US$]]15,631. None of the population or families were below the [[poverty line]].{{citation needed|date=March 2013}}

